{"_id":"1Q6PTMhAVORiOykX","name":"_Overview","content":"<p>Emerule is a \"Location Module\"; it is designed to depict the Emerule manor and village located in Fethael Hundred, Nephshire, kingdom of Kaldor, on the island of Hârn in the <a href=\"https://columbiagames.com/harnworld/\">HârnWorld fantasy setting</a>; however, this manor and village could be adapted to exist anywhere in any fantasy setting.</p>\n<p>This module is based on the Emerule manor article from \"<a href=\"https://www.lythia.com/fethael-hundred/manors.html\">Fethael Hundred Manors</a>\" fanon; please see @Compendium[hm-loc-emerule.journals.hDdG1O93oKOL3EJm]{Credits} for more information.</p>\n<p>This module details all of the households, including interior plans of the manor.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<h2>Using this module with Non-HârnMaster systems</h2>\n<p>This entire module is system-agnostic.  See the section below on NPCs for details about the residents; these details may be used to generate appropriate statistics for your game system.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<h2>Using the Scenes</h2>\n<p>A number of scenes are provided representing maps. These scenes depict both internal and external areas; internal areas are generally set at a 5-foot grid spacing, while exterior areas use much larger scaling. The following subsections describe some common elements of these scenes.</p>\n<h3>Map Notes</h3>\n<p>The scenes make extensive use of Map Notes to provide detailed description of important areas in the scenes. To view these map notes, click on the \"bookmark icon\" in the canvas toolbar. Map notes are not visible to players, only to the GM.</p>\n<h3>Text and Markings</h3>\n<p>In various areas text and or markings have been provided in the scenes to assist the GM. Generally this information is set to only be visible to the GM.</p>\n<h3>Stairs</h3>\n<p>Some stairs may have an arrow indicating the direction the stairs descend. When present these arrows are visible to all players.</p>\n<h3>Lighting</h3>\n<p>To control ambient lighting, use the \"darkness\" setting for the scene.</p>\n<p>All scenes have been setup with Unrestricted Vision Range enabled, with a Vision Limitation Threshold set to 0.7. This allows all areas of the scene to be lit during the day, but vision is limited and lights are required at night.</p>\n<p>Internal lamps and candle lights have been placed in indoor areas. These lights have been set to enable when the \"darkness\" setting is ≥ 0.2, that is, just after things start becoming dim.</p>\n<p>Hârn has a cool climate, so all fireplaces and braziers are constantly lit.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<h2>Recommended Modules</h2>\n<p>The following modules, although not required, are highly recommended to enhance this module:</p>\n<p><strong>Compendium Folders: </strong>Due to the large number of journal entries in this module, these journal entries have been organized into sub-folders using Compendium Folders. If Compendium Folders is not used, these will all show up as a single long list of Journal Entries in the compendium. As long as you follow the links starting with the _Overview journal entry, it should not be necessary to navigate the compendium, but if you want to navigate through the Journal Entries yourself, having Compendium Folders will greately simplify this task.</p>\n<p><strong>Backgroundless Pins:</strong> The map note icons all have a dark grey background; with this module, that background disappears. This may increase your enjoyment of the maps.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p> </p>\n<h2>Background Information</h2>\n<p>For historical, political, and recent events, see @Compendium[hm-loc-emerule.journals.3ZEAWp89Q8kOOh4F]{Settlement Information}.</p>\n<p>For additional adventures in and around Emerule, see @Compendium[hm-loc-emerule.journals.tzURBjoTSgEUMK3F]{Adventure Hooks}.</p>\n<p>Emerule is the hunting lodge for the Indamas.  For details about the annual hunting gathering, see @Compendium[hm-loc-emerule.journals.Qr4YL55aQETbfirw]{Boar Hunting with the Indama Clan}.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<h2>Village Details</h2>\n<p>The tiny manor sits on a small rise above the Omin River. The wattle and daub dwellings cluster in a thin line along the riverside of the rutted track. A small bridge is used when spring rains wash out the much larger ford.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>@Compendium[hm-loc-emerule.journals.qQDezDeNu5g3hUAE]{[1] Cottar Durel Arsarl}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[hm-loc-emerule.journals.qWsiawhssiM2hd7h]{[2] Half-Villein Netokra Haral}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[hm-loc-emerule.journals.d9llHc4AoqHBzgtW]{[3] Half-Villein Aratha Krandar}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[hm-loc-emerule.journals.oZNOGCcoPty20HeS]{[4] Half-Villein (Woodward) Gerl Tyun}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[hm-loc-emerule.journals.tWBeHIYiQB6wBg1V]{[5] Half-Villein Alona Dyren}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[hm-loc-emerule.journals.ee0aG2aSr8MZxkcb]{[6] Half-Villein Wasinila Nelt}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[hm-loc-emerule.journals.y0vMyXk8hAg5jM5q]{[7] Charcoaler Anderin Asaka}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[hm-loc-emerule.journals.r0SPay9RL9s5MbDa]{[8] Half-Villein Torrynë Berma}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[hm-loc-emerule.journals.v8tqPo6GFhtNoWaC]{[9] Villein Thadotes Faleren}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[hm-loc-emerule.journals.QW7Z1lPYaR96kryT]{[10] Villein Arnil Krandar}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[hm-loc-emerule.journals.zmjOy82fxdU5ghjH]{[11] Half-Villein Ledis Haral}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[hm-loc-emerule.journals.IK80ekcs0ewEAtXj]{[12] Yeoman Erphis Berma}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[hm-loc-emerule.journals.zRqzHyNw4MsCFS7V]{[13] Half-Villein (Beadle) Lanasai Nelt}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[hm-loc-emerule.journals.VKkIBEJ6Fq1UbbmJ]{[14] Villein (Reeve) Taran Krandar}</li>\n</ul>\n<p> </p>\n<h2>Manor House</h2>\n<p>The old fortified bailey has stood guard over the river for years. The tower was rebuilt in stone over 100 years ago but the buildings in the bailey are torn down and renovated at least once or twice a decade, depending on weather and fire.</p>\n<p>Sir Marby keeps the manor and its hall clean, ready for the Baron’s next hunting trip or Lady Lysella’s next suitor.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>@Compendium[hm-loc-emerule.journals.rQRWjihIJ94RMcKE]{[A] The Gatehouse}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[hm-loc-emerule.journals.MmK3RIQfvipeeZoe]{[B] The Stable}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[hm-loc-emerule.journals.74MKHFR57r7sdjCP]{[C] The Smithy}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[hm-loc-emerule.journals.egTbHiLeo5WXtJjZ]{[D1] Tower Hill}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[hm-loc-emerule.journals.HcQj1noXBdXfTsoU]{[D2] Cellar}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[hm-loc-emerule.journals.jjo5GpTYlVVmIILv]{[D3] Sir Marby’s Chamber}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[hm-loc-emerule.journals.PPdHl0rhjFrylMRr]{[E1] The Kitchen}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[hm-loc-emerule.journals.ZZ66gm6xooUj7U6U]{[E2] Kitchen Postern Gate}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[hm-loc-emerule.journals.eGgwFtQAAR324gLE]{[F] The Brewhouse}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[hm-loc-emerule.journals.KsyqACXWWLBMhnWE]{[G1] The Storeroom and Armory}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[hm-loc-emerule.journals.mOy7eEKRYPXz5sQZ]{[G2] The Mews}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[hm-loc-emerule.journals.OZehKqKeb4uyiTIp]{[G3] The Great Hall}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[hm-loc-emerule.journals.TNiY2bUerO8rGUKp]{[G4] Lord's Chambers}</li>\n</ul>\n<p> </p>\n<h3>Residents</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>@Compendium[hm-loc-emerule.journals.f3z2JZBseiPvyZVs]{Sir Marby “Blue Dog” Lournay}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[hm-loc-emerule.journals.ePhDZQmtr8JHYkTb]{Lady Lysella Indama}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[hm-loc-emerule.journals.PrLD9Zn2RgfVY6YP]{Lady Erlyn Immen}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[hm-loc-emerule.journals.5Lr4gWZpIzu63W8w]{Squire Gaibin Asane}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[hm-loc-emerule.journals.atqWXdA8OKrk1Qvm]{Wilan Baral}</li>\n</ul>\n<p> </p>\n<h3>Staff</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>@Compendium[hm-loc-emerule.journals.K88mNr8deronTJSY]{Amrenë Kleve} - Scullery maid</li>\n<li>@Compendium[hm-loc-emerule.journals.FtWAWbcRj7bcf71p]{Clas Gweren} - Blacksmith</li>\n<li>@Compendium[hm-loc-emerule.journals.9DrDc25r3BhTBJJ1]{Jilenia Gweren} - Alewife</li>\n<li>@Compendium[hm-loc-emerule.journals.GM2tbBtdqBoV5KJp]{Klarlin Berma} - Cook and Head Housekeeper</li>\n<li>@Compendium[hm-loc-emerule.journals.WsVC2ouOoVRH71P0]{Kordin Artusiel} - Huntsman</li>\n<li>@Compendium[hm-loc-emerule.journals.52zLckRQqMwFiMfe]{Nesnia Urdel} - Baker</li>\n<li>@Compendium[hm-loc-emerule.journals.fL6KymiW9zfHvUS1]{Petry Ekutoshi} - Chamberlain</li>\n</ul>\n<p> </p>\n<h2>NPCs</h2>\n<table border=\"1\">\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th style=\"width:6em\">Loc</th>\n<th style=\"width:10em\">Name</th>\n<th style=\"width:13em\">Occupation</th>\n<th>Journal</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>5</td>\n<td>Alona Dyren</td>\n<td>Half-Villein</td>\n<td>@Compendium[hm-loc-emerule.journals.tWBeHIYiQB6wBg1V]{[5] Half-Villein Alona Dyren}</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Manor</td>\n<td>Amrenë Kleve</td>\n<td>Scullery Maid</td>\n<td>@Compendium[hm-loc-emerule.journals.K88mNr8deronTJSY]{Amrenë Kleve}</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>3</td>\n<td>Aratha Krandar</td>\n<td>Half-Villein</td>\n<td>@Compendium[hm-loc-emerule.journals.d9llHc4AoqHBzgtW]{[3] Half-Villein Aratha Krandar}</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>10</td>\n<td>Arnil Krandar</td>\n<td>Villein</td>\n<td>@Compendium[hm-loc-emerule.journals.QW7Z1lPYaR96kryT]{[10] Villein Arnil Krandar}</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Manor</td>\n<td>Clas Gweren</td>\n<td>Blacksmith</td>\n<td>@Compendium[hm-loc-emerule.journals.FtWAWbcRj7bcf71p]{Clas Gweren}</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>1</td>\n<td>Durel Arsarl</td>\n<td>Cottar</td>\n<td>@Compendium[hm-loc-emerule.journals.qQDezDeNu5g3hUAE]{[1] Cottar Durel Arsarl}</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>12</td>\n<td>Erphis Berma</td>\n<td>Yeoman</td>\n<td>@Compendium[hm-loc-emerule.journals.IK80ekcs0ewEAtXj]{[12] Yeoman Erphis Berma}</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Manor</td>\n<td>Gaibin Asane</td>\n<td>Sir Marby's Squire</td>\n<td>@Compendium[hm-loc-emerule.journals.5Lr4gWZpIzu63W8w]{Squire Gaibin Asane}</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>4</td>\n<td>Gerl Tyun</td>\n<td>Half-Villein (Woodward)</td>\n<td>@Compendium[hm-loc-emerule.journals.oZNOGCcoPty20HeS]{[4] Half-Villein (Woodward) Gerl Tyun}</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Manor</td>\n<td>Jilenia Gweren</td>\n<td>Cook/Alewife</td>\n<td>@Compendium[hm-loc-emerule.journals.9DrDc25r3BhTBJJ1]{Jilenia Gweren}</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Manor</td>\n<td>Klarlin Berma</td>\n<td>Cook and Housekeeper</td>\n<td>@Compendium[hm-loc-emerule.journals.GM2tbBtdqBoV5KJp]{Klarlin Berma}</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Manor</td>\n<td>Kordin Artusiel</td>\n<td>Huntsman</td>\n<td>@Compendium[hm-loc-emerule.journals.WsVC2ouOoVRH71P0]{Kordin Artusiel}</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Manor</td>\n<td>Lady Erlyn Immen</td>\n<td> </td>\n<td>@Compendium[hm-loc-emerule.journals.PrLD9Zn2RgfVY6YP]{Lady Erlyn Immen}</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Manor</td>\n<td>Lady Lysella Indama</td>\n<td> </td>\n<td>@Compendium[hm-loc-emerule.journals.ePhDZQmtr8JHYkTb]{Lady Lysella Indama}</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>13</td>\n<td>Lanasai Nelt</td>\n<td>Half-Villein (Beadle)</td>\n<td>@Compendium[hm-loc-emerule.journals.zRqzHyNw4MsCFS7V]{[13] Half-Villein (Beadle) Lanasai Nelt}</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>11</td>\n<td>Ledis Haral</td>\n<td>Half-Villein</td>\n<td>@Compendium[hm-loc-emerule.journals.zmjOy82fxdU5ghjH]{[11] Half-Villein Ledis Haral}</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Manor</td>\n<td>Nesnia Urdel</td>\n<td>Baker</td>\n<td>@Compendium[hm-loc-emerule.journals.52zLckRQqMwFiMfe]{Nesnia Urdel}</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>2</td>\n<td>Netokra Haral</td>\n<td>Half-Villein</td>\n<td>@Compendium[hm-loc-emerule.journals.qWsiawhssiM2hd7h]{[2] Half-Villein Netokra Haral}</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Manor</td>\n<td>Petry Ekutoshi</td>\n<td>Chamberlain</td>\n<td>@Compendium[hm-loc-emerule.journals.fL6KymiW9zfHvUS1]{Petry Ekutoshi}</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Manor</td>\n<td>Sir Marby \"Blue Dog\" Lournay</td>\n<td>Lord of Emerule</td>\n<td>@Compendium[hm-loc-emerule.journals.f3z2JZBseiPvyZVs]{Sir Marby “Blue Dog” Lournay}</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>14</td>\n<td>Taran Krandar</td>\n<td>Villein (Reeve)</td>\n<td>@Compendium[hm-loc-emerule.journals.VKkIBEJ6Fq1UbbmJ]{[14] Villein (Reeve) Taran Krandar}</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>9</td>\n<td>Thadotes Faleren</td>\n<td>Villein</td>\n<td>@Compendium[hm-loc-emerule.journals.v8tqPo6GFhtNoWaC]{[9] Villein Thadotes Faleren}</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>8</td>\n<td>Torrynë Berma</td>\n<td>Half-Villein</td>\n<td>@Compendium[hm-loc-emerule.journals.r0SPay9RL9s5MbDa]{[8] Half-Villein Torrynë Berma}</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>6</td>\n<td>Wasinila Nelt</td>\n<td>Half-Villein</td>\n<td>@Compendium[hm-loc-emerule.journals.ee0aG2aSr8MZxkcb]{[6] Half-Villein Wasinila Nelt}</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Manor</td>\n<td>Wilan Baral</td>\n<td>Lady Lysella's Page</td>\n<td>@Compendium[hm-loc-emerule.journals.atqWXdA8OKrk1Qvm]{Wilan Baral}</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p> </p>\n<h2>Schedule of Events</h2>\n<p>Hall moot held on the second Second Day (day 12) of each month.</p>\n<p>This represents Sir Marby's schedule. If not otherwise indicated, Sir Marby would be located in Emerule.</p>\n<table border=\"1\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<th style=\"width:10em\">...Tenday...</th>\n<th style=\"width:10em\">Sir Marby (Emerule)</th>\n<th style=\"width:10em\">Events</th>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Nuzyael 1</td>\n<td>Emerule</td>\n<td> </td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Nuzyael 2</td>\n<td> </td>\n<td> </td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Nuzyael 3</td>\n<td> </td>\n<td> </td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Peonu 1</td>\n<td>Lethyl</td>\n<td>(3)</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Peonu 2</td>\n<td>Emerule</td>\n<td> </td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Peonu 3</td>\n<td> </td>\n<td> </td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Kelen 1</td>\n<td> </td>\n<td>Wool Fair</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Kelen 2</td>\n<td>Getha</td>\n<td>Getha Fair</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Kelen 3</td>\n<td>Emerule</td>\n<td> </td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Nolus 1</td>\n<td>Drilen</td>\n<td>Tashal Fair</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Nolus 2</td>\n<td>Jenkald</td>\n<td> </td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Nolus 3</td>\n<td>Tashal</td>\n<td> </td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Larane 1</td>\n<td>Olokand</td>\n<td>Chelebin Tourney</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Larane 2</td>\n<td>Olokand</td>\n<td>Chelebin Tourney</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Larane 3</td>\n<td> </td>\n<td> </td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Agrazhar 1</td>\n<td>Jenkald</td>\n<td>(2)</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Agrazhar 2</td>\n<td>Emerule</td>\n<td> </td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Agrazhar 3</td>\n<td> </td>\n<td> </td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Azura 1</td>\n<td> </td>\n<td>Kiban Fair</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Azura 2</td>\n<td> </td>\n<td> </td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Azura 3</td>\n<td> </td>\n<td> </td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Halane 1</td>\n<td> </td>\n<td> </td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Halane 2</td>\n<td> </td>\n<td> </td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Halane 3</td>\n<td>Getha</td>\n<td>(4)</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Savor 1</td>\n<td>Lethyl</td>\n<td>(3)</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Savor 2</td>\n<td>Emerule</td>\n<td>(1)</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Savor 3</td>\n<td> </td>\n<td> </td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Ilvin 1</td>\n<td> </td>\n<td> </td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Ilvin 2</td>\n<td> </td>\n<td> </td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Ilvin 3</td>\n<td> </td>\n<td> </td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Navek 1</td>\n<td> </td>\n<td> </td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Navek 2</td>\n<td> </td>\n<td> </td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Navek 3</td>\n<td> </td>\n<td> </td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Morgat 1</td>\n<td> </td>\n<td> </td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Morgat 2</td>\n<td> </td>\n<td> </td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Morgat 3</td>\n<td> </td>\n<td> </td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p> </p>\n<p>(1) The Indama annual boar hunt is hosted at Emerule, small manor in the western part of the Fethael hundred. Some politics. Lots of hunting.</p>\n<p>(2) As part of his progress around the kingdom, the Serekela attends the mass of St. Orthas’ Day at Getha or perhaps (even better) Jenkald.</p>\n<p>(3) All of the Indamas come to Lethyl to celebrate St. Valamin’s Day and St. Syrele’s Feast. St. Syrele’s is considered the start of the family’s annual hunt.</p>\n<p>(4) The annual tax recording is done during the end of Halane/beginning of Savor. Lords like Sir Eadwin meet with their vassals and then all proceed to Getha to meet with the Baron.</p>","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"Rn9jkHilxPKp2kf5":3},"flags":{"entityorder":{"order":400000},"scene-packer":{"sourceId":"Jour